\section{Data post-processing}

Data were sequenced on 1 lane on the same flowcell with an Illumina Hiseq platform 100-read length paired-end in IGBMC (S17140 project). 
MRDR5 (14,082,768 reads after adapters removal were delivered) and MRDR6 (99,954,850 reads after adapters removal were delivered) paired files were first used as they contain resp. female and male DNA in a pool sequencing. 
The encoding of quality values is Sanger / Illumina 1.9 format.\\
See doc directory for reports produced by IGBMC. Forward (R1) reads are less than reverse (R2) reads. 


%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{FastQC}

\begin{itemize}
  \item adapter trimming. This was performed by IGBMC and not done, indeed there is no contamination in adapter as regards FASTQ reports. 
  \item quality of sequencing. Data are good quality data: mean(QPhred), both ends. There is a slightly decrease of quality at the end of the reads but not major issue and we keep all reads whatherver the position on the flowcell. Reverse reads have lower quality and we need to make pairs again.  
  \item bp content. FIrst 6 bp are biased in bp content probabky due to experimental protocole (random hexamer fixation on DNA fragments), this does not required trimming. However, there is 2 modes as regards the GC content and IGBMC reports previously noted a contamination in E. coli (= worms food). This suggest to mapp against E. coli to remove this contamination.
\end{itemize}



%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\subsection{Data cleaning}

We used cutadapt to trim N ends and tails qith quality lower than 20. No other filter was applied. 


